1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,433
(All characters, organizations,
and events in this drama are fictitious.)

2
00:00:01,433 --> 00:00:02,700
(Filming complied with guidelines
for children, youth, and animals.)

3
00:00:05,533 --> 00:00:06,933
(Episode 35)

4
00:00:14,833 --> 00:00:15,833
Found you.

5
00:00:25,649 --> 00:00:26,649
My goodness!

6
00:00:30,538 --> 00:00:32,525
- Are you okay?
- Yes, I'm okay.

7
00:00:35,771 --> 00:00:37,435
You call that okay?

8
00:00:45,860 --> 00:00:46,860
That must hurt.

9
00:01:00,333 --> 00:01:01,633
You're so careless.

10
00:01:03,801 --> 00:01:06,219
Why did you suddenly show up like that?

11
00:01:06,501 --> 00:01:07,923
Do you know how startled I was?

12
00:01:18,581 --> 00:01:20,987
What's wrong?

13
00:01:29,776 --> 00:01:31,209
What's this?

14
00:01:33,112 --> 00:01:35,117
It's my lucky charm. Why?

15
00:01:35,713 --> 00:01:37,909
Your lucky charm? Let me see.

16
00:01:38,695 --> 00:01:40,325
Where did you get this?

17
00:01:40,859 --> 00:01:43,992
My first love gave it to me. Why?

18
00:01:44,154 --> 00:01:45,221
Your first love?

19
00:01:45,863 --> 00:01:47,163
Yes, my first love.

20
00:01:49,006 --> 00:01:52,181
Wasn't there a name written
on the flagpole?

21
00:01:53,352 --> 00:01:57,781
Yes, was it Han Byeol? No, Han Gyeol...

22
00:01:59,387 --> 00:02:00,645
But how do you know that?

23
00:02:04,123 --> 00:02:06,293
Don't tell me
you're that boy from back then!

24
00:02:06,629 --> 00:02:09,472
Are you okay? That must hurt.

25
00:02:17,928 --> 00:02:20,403
Stick this in here.

26
00:02:22,693 --> 00:02:23,693
What do I do?

27
00:02:23,693 --> 00:02:26,653
It's okay.
If it collapses, we can rebuild it.

28
00:02:27,447 --> 00:02:29,448
This is a lucky flag.

29
00:02:29,800 --> 00:02:31,779
My dad made it for me.

30
00:02:32,109 --> 00:02:33,456
If you have it,

31
00:02:34,147 --> 00:02:36,749
you won't be scared when you're alone,
and it gives you courage.

32
00:02:37,539 --> 00:02:38,995
Give it back next time we meet.

33
00:02:39,552 --> 00:02:41,944
I come here every Saturday.

34
00:02:42,920 --> 00:02:45,979
Next time, I'll make you a house
out of ice cream sticks.

35
00:02:46,335 --> 00:02:47,335
Bye.

36
00:02:48,829 --> 00:02:50,483
No way. How...

37
00:02:50,752 --> 00:02:52,901
How could that boy be you, Team Manager?

38
00:02:53,080 --> 00:02:55,797
I know, right?
That little kid was you, Ms. Cho Eun Ae?

39
00:02:56,463 --> 00:02:57,796
Unbelievable.

40
00:02:58,973 --> 00:03:02,485
But the kid I knew...

41
00:03:02,485 --> 00:03:04,555
was really cute and adorable.

42
00:03:05,225 --> 00:03:07,653
How did you turn out like this?

43
00:03:08,093 --> 00:03:09,384
Look who's talking.

44
00:03:09,688 --> 00:03:11,955
That boy was so brave and cool back then.

45
00:03:12,666 --> 00:03:13,666
Now...

46
00:03:16,667 --> 00:03:18,965
I was brave and cool, wasn't I?

47
00:03:19,533 --> 00:03:21,416
So that's why I was your first love.

48
00:03:21,827 --> 00:03:25,208
First love? I was only five back then.

49
00:03:25,435 --> 00:03:26,648
Is something wrong with my hearing?

50
00:03:27,024 --> 00:03:29,717
I'm pretty sure you said "first love."

51
00:03:30,003 --> 00:03:32,749
That's just how I put it.

52
00:03:33,665 --> 00:03:35,419
But why did you change your name?

53
00:03:35,690 --> 00:03:37,590
I thought
your last name was Han back then.

54
00:03:38,035 --> 00:03:40,120
So you were originally Ko Han Gyeol.

55
00:03:41,456 --> 00:03:43,043
Well, yes...

56
00:03:47,125 --> 00:03:49,307
You liar. You trickster.

57
00:03:49,485 --> 00:03:52,037
What? Liar? Trickster?

58
00:03:52,464 --> 00:03:55,488
You said you came here every Saturday.

59
00:03:56,085 --> 00:03:58,585
Do you know how long I waited here
every Saturday?

60
00:04:00,069 --> 00:04:02,813
- You waited for me?
- Yes.

61
00:04:03,181 --> 00:04:06,445
After a while, I even went
to that apartment construction site.

62
00:04:07,904 --> 00:04:10,517
Tell me. Why didn't you keep your promise?

63
00:04:11,749 --> 00:04:15,144
When did I ever make that kind of promise?

64
00:04:17,257 --> 00:04:18,464
This is ridiculous.

65
00:04:18,908 --> 00:04:20,841
You're talking as if I'm making this up.

66
00:04:24,203 --> 00:04:27,971
You said your dad was throwing you
a birthday party that day. Did it go well?

67
00:04:30,044 --> 00:04:31,683
Yes, it did.

68
00:04:33,360 --> 00:04:36,315
So that person was CEO Ko Dae Chi.

69
00:04:37,608 --> 00:04:39,232
What a small world.

70
00:04:45,900 --> 00:04:46,900
What is it?

71
00:04:47,233 --> 00:04:49,013
Come here.

72
00:04:52,371 --> 00:04:55,029
The password was 000.

73
00:04:55,344 --> 00:04:57,861
It's so simple, it puts me to shame.

74
00:04:57,861 --> 00:04:59,437
Stop. Freeze.

75
00:05:00,704 --> 00:05:03,851
Crystal, I don't think this is right.

76
00:05:03,984 --> 00:05:07,173
You said we need to know the enemy
and ourselves to win.

77
00:05:08,485 --> 00:05:12,251
Well, we need to know
what Gyeol will do for the second round...

78
00:05:12,251 --> 00:05:13,997
to come up with a plan, right?

79
00:05:13,997 --> 00:05:16,013
- That goes without saying.
- Right.

80
00:05:17,947 --> 00:05:19,147
- You know for sure, right?
- Yes.

81
00:05:19,655 --> 00:05:21,408
What are you two doing here?

82
00:05:21,952 --> 00:05:23,139
You startled me.

83
00:05:24,203 --> 00:05:25,373
What are we doing?

84
00:05:25,373 --> 00:05:27,912
Wait, what were we doing here?

85
00:05:28,228 --> 00:05:29,773
What do you mean, what?

86
00:05:30,072 --> 00:05:33,381
We're just trying to get some info
in case Gyeol takes your spot. Why?

87
00:05:35,636 --> 00:05:38,236
Stop what you're doing and come out.
Let's talk in my room.

88
00:05:48,061 --> 00:05:51,240
I've told you several times, haven't I?
Please trust me.

89
00:05:52,685 --> 00:05:54,539
Of course we trust you. Who said we don't?

90
00:05:55,131 --> 00:05:56,164
Then why?

91
00:05:58,589 --> 00:06:00,883
What are you trying to get
from Gyeol's laptop?

92
00:06:00,883 --> 00:06:04,333
You know, that "Know your enemy" thing...

93
00:06:04,811 --> 00:06:07,629
I said I don't need anything,
so why are you doing this?

94
00:06:07,963 --> 00:06:10,277
Are you getting full of yourself?

95
00:06:10,517 --> 00:06:12,411
If you mess up...

96
00:06:12,411 --> 00:06:16,080
Then I'll be the one to fall,
and I'll be the one to step back.

97
00:06:16,435 --> 00:06:20,180
I'm going to compete
with Gyeol fairly this time.

98
00:06:20,180 --> 00:06:21,835
I told you before, Dad!

99
00:06:22,155 --> 00:06:23,455
You did, yes.

100
00:06:23,963 --> 00:06:26,979
So from now on, I'm neutral. Neutral gear.

101
00:06:28,592 --> 00:06:30,697
How can you be so spineless?

102
00:06:30,697 --> 00:06:33,707
Just a moment ago, you were on my side,
and now you're siding with Min Ho?

103
00:06:34,624 --> 00:06:37,643
Hey, didn't you see
your grandpa's eyes last time?

104
00:06:38,068 --> 00:06:40,735
It's not over till it's over.

105
00:06:41,256 --> 00:06:43,037
Gyeol has already...

106
00:06:43,037 --> 00:06:44,685
Please stop talking about Gyeol!

107
00:06:47,413 --> 00:06:48,413
Just leave already.

108
00:06:49,595 --> 00:06:51,687
We were about to leave. Retreat.

109
00:06:51,687 --> 00:06:52,687
All right, retreat.

110
00:06:52,687 --> 00:06:53,820
Hurry up and go.

111
00:07:13,989 --> 00:07:15,240
Where have you been?

112
00:07:16,165 --> 00:07:18,611
Mom, did you clean my desk?

113
00:07:19,016 --> 00:07:20,016
No, why?

114
00:07:20,860 --> 00:07:22,445
How can you be like that?

115
00:07:22,968 --> 00:07:25,373
I know Min Ho dotes on you, but still...

116
00:07:25,827 --> 00:07:27,931
Did Chief Ko come into my room?

117
00:07:30,074 --> 00:07:32,077
He wanted to see your childhood photos,
so just for a moment.

118
00:07:32,784 --> 00:07:35,061
- Mom, seriously!
- What?

119
00:07:35,445 --> 00:07:37,163
If you weren't my daughter...

120
00:07:38,305 --> 00:07:41,005
Who would put up with that temper?

121
00:07:53,472 --> 00:07:55,709
But isn't it amazing
the more you think about it?

122
00:07:56,155 --> 00:07:58,288
How could we meet again like this?

123
00:07:58,733 --> 00:08:01,880
More than that, I'm amazed...

124
00:08:01,880 --> 00:08:03,408
that you still have that clover piece.

125
00:08:03,909 --> 00:08:05,064
What's this?

126
00:08:05,481 --> 00:08:07,971
Your tone's been getting more casual
since earlier.

127
00:08:08,809 --> 00:08:10,021
Because I'm older.

128
00:08:10,435 --> 00:08:13,360
That brave and cool first love.

129
00:08:14,267 --> 00:08:16,317
That's all in the past.

130
00:08:17,093 --> 00:08:19,733
You're not going to ask for this back,
are you?

131
00:08:20,057 --> 00:08:21,261
I can't do without this.

132
00:08:22,015 --> 00:08:23,115
All right.

133
00:08:25,725 --> 00:08:28,005
But what's going on?

134
00:08:28,779 --> 00:08:29,879
What?

135
00:08:30,568 --> 00:08:33,299
You look a bit different from usual today.

136
00:08:33,721 --> 00:08:34,896
Why are you so dressed up?

137
00:08:35,413 --> 00:08:37,848
What? Who's dressed up?

138
00:08:38,435 --> 00:08:41,600
I usually wear this at home.

139
00:08:43,315 --> 00:08:46,067
So you dress like this casually at home?

140
00:08:47,023 --> 00:08:49,392
What I wear at home
is none of your business.

141
00:08:50,680 --> 00:08:53,083
- Go on inside.
- Yes, you should go too.

142
00:08:54,136 --> 00:08:57,795
Right, what did you urgently want
to discuss about the second round?

143
00:08:57,795 --> 00:08:58,984
We didn't get to talk about it.

144
00:08:58,984 --> 00:09:01,633
Let's talk about it at work on Monday.

145
00:09:01,633 --> 00:09:03,147
All right. Get home safely.

146
00:09:04,052 --> 00:09:05,052
Goodbye.

147
00:09:12,123 --> 00:09:13,387
What a coincidence.

148
00:09:19,300 --> 00:09:20,533
(Room for rent, Deposit - 10,000 dollars,
Rent - 500 dollars)

149
00:09:22,123 --> 00:09:23,223
A 10,000-dollar deposit
and a 500-dollar rent?

150
00:09:25,752 --> 00:09:27,435
Is that cheap?

151
00:09:35,133 --> 00:09:36,900
(Room for rent, Deposit - 10,000 dollars,
Rent - 500 dollars)

152
00:09:46,329 --> 00:09:47,403
It's been so long...

153
00:09:47,715 --> 00:09:51,525
since the whole family sat together
for a meal like this.

154
00:09:51,776 --> 00:09:55,520
Since Dad became unemployed...
No, since he lost his job,

155
00:09:55,520 --> 00:09:57,912
this is the first time.

156
00:09:59,433 --> 00:10:03,392
Bit Na, your bright memory is impressive,

157
00:10:03,813 --> 00:10:06,413
but do you really have to shine a light
on Dad's dark past too?

158
00:10:07,152 --> 00:10:10,776
So you got a job
at a children's writing cram school?

159
00:10:11,171 --> 00:10:14,805
Yes, even though
it's a small neighborhood cram school,

160
00:10:14,805 --> 00:10:16,538
it's very rewarding and enjoyable.

161
00:10:17,281 --> 00:10:19,061
Being with children full of pure hearts...

162
00:10:19,501 --> 00:10:21,869
and limitless imagination...

163
00:10:22,396 --> 00:10:24,117
makes me feel like
I've gone back to those days.

164
00:10:26,829 --> 00:10:29,789
Ji Seon, could you bring more japchae?

165
00:10:30,069 --> 00:10:31,709
Sorry? Right, okay.

166
00:10:36,437 --> 00:10:39,203
Please, be more mindful.

167
00:10:41,061 --> 00:10:42,704
Am I not mindful?

168
00:10:42,877 --> 00:10:45,624
Well, you're not exactly known for that.

169
00:10:45,992 --> 00:10:49,403
Don't talk like you're any better.
You're just as clueless, you know?

170
00:10:49,969 --> 00:10:51,240
Well, what can you do?

171
00:10:51,632 --> 00:10:54,237
You all take after me.

172
00:10:55,400 --> 00:10:58,621
Right? Isn't that so?

173
00:11:00,792 --> 00:11:03,107
All right, let's eat.

174
00:11:03,256 --> 00:11:04,552
Eat up.

175
00:11:05,355 --> 00:11:08,347
You're not satisfied
with his cram school job, are you?

176
00:11:10,832 --> 00:11:14,171
Since he lost his job,
he has to earn money,

177
00:11:14,740 --> 00:11:16,173
so I understand he has no choice.

178
00:11:17,824 --> 00:11:21,139
You heard him.
He says it's rewarding and enjoyable.

179
00:11:22,455 --> 00:11:25,411
I wonder if he still plans
to return to teaching at a university.

180
00:11:27,563 --> 00:11:30,477
I still stand by what I said.

181
00:11:31,825 --> 00:11:33,625
- Sorry?
- I ended up...

182
00:11:34,085 --> 00:11:35,720
coming back home like this,

183
00:11:36,168 --> 00:11:40,011
but you're still young,
so make the right decision.

184
00:11:40,900 --> 00:11:44,685
Don't worry about what anyone thinks,
and think only about your life.

185
00:11:46,933 --> 00:11:48,005
- Let's go.
- Okay.

186
00:11:51,100 --> 00:11:53,619
Mom's japchae really is the best.

187
00:11:53,619 --> 00:11:55,700
I love your zucchini pancakes, Mom.

188
00:11:55,700 --> 00:11:57,059
- Eat a lot.
- Same here.

189
00:11:58,848 --> 00:12:02,947
All right,
I have something to say to all of you.

190
00:12:03,571 --> 00:12:06,437
In life, you can lose your job,

191
00:12:06,437 --> 00:12:09,488
get scammed, or have accidents.

192
00:12:10,236 --> 00:12:12,195
From now on,
if anyone is going through a hard time,

193
00:12:12,411 --> 00:12:15,744
don't keep it bottled up.
Just talk about it.

194
00:12:16,552 --> 00:12:19,379
We kept things quiet
and hid things in consideration,

195
00:12:19,644 --> 00:12:21,344
and look what almost happened
to our family.

196
00:12:23,728 --> 00:12:26,955
So there should be no secrets
among family, right?

197
00:12:28,123 --> 00:12:31,739
You catch on the fastest, Bit Na.

198
00:12:32,931 --> 00:12:35,928
Dad, actually, this morning,

199
00:12:35,928 --> 00:12:38,856
the omelet rice you made wasn't that good,

200
00:12:39,413 --> 00:12:41,700
but I said it was
because I didn't want to disappoint you.

201
00:12:46,241 --> 00:12:49,277
Family means sharing everything.

202
00:12:49,557 --> 00:12:51,373
Not just the good things,

203
00:12:51,373 --> 00:12:54,573
but the hard, exhausting,
and painful things too.

204
00:12:55,264 --> 00:12:57,507
Right, I'll start with myself.

205
00:12:57,507 --> 00:13:00,832
From now on, I won't carry burdens alone.

206
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:03,720
I'll do the same right away.

207
00:13:04,712 --> 00:13:07,715
I made it seem like I was teaching
at a university, not a cram school,

208
00:13:07,715 --> 00:13:08,907
and I almost got divorced because of it.

209
00:13:08,907 --> 00:13:10,024
- Seriously...
- Eun Hyeong,

210
00:13:10,024 --> 00:13:12,237
isn't that too much to do to your wife?

211
00:13:12,237 --> 00:13:16,269
Exactly. You scolded me
for hiding that I dropped out.

212
00:13:16,925 --> 00:13:19,392
You dropped out? When?

213
00:13:19,941 --> 00:13:21,008
A while ago.

214
00:13:21,707 --> 00:13:24,563
Everyone, don't lose confidence
just because things don't go as planned.

215
00:13:24,563 --> 00:13:27,525
Hold your heads high.

216
00:13:28,073 --> 00:13:30,673
With a family like this,
what's there to be afraid of?

217
00:13:31,808 --> 00:13:35,069
Everyone,
pick up the glass in front of you.

218
00:13:35,847 --> 00:13:39,277
I'll lead, so shout, "Don't be scared."

219
00:13:40,363 --> 00:13:41,463
Our family!

220
00:13:41,463 --> 00:13:43,100
- Don't be scared!
- Don't be scared!

221
00:13:44,817 --> 00:13:47,141
- Don't be scared!
- Don't be scared!

222
00:13:48,623 --> 00:13:49,623
Where's Seung Ri?

223
00:13:49,907 --> 00:13:50,940
I don't know.

224
00:13:51,371 --> 00:13:54,091
She's in a bad mood
and locked herself in her room.

225
00:13:54,968 --> 00:13:58,192
You shouldn't have invited Chief Ko
without asking.

226
00:13:58,421 --> 00:13:59,677
Someone had to step in.

227
00:14:00,411 --> 00:14:03,099
No matter how much effort
she puts into Gyeol...

228
00:14:03,099 --> 00:14:05,477
Things will go as they're meant to.

229
00:14:05,853 --> 00:14:07,811
Can you really change that?

230
00:14:11,582 --> 00:14:13,507
What are you doing? You keep fidgeting.

231
00:14:13,685 --> 00:14:15,773
Are your phones all fine?

232
00:14:17,500 --> 00:14:22,064
I mean, my phone is fine.
Why am I not getting a call?

233
00:14:24,197 --> 00:14:26,430
It's here. It's the writer.

234
00:14:27,533 --> 00:14:30,717
Really? Answer it. Put it on speaker.

235
00:14:30,944 --> 00:14:32,931
Wait, I'm nervous.

236
00:14:41,872 --> 00:14:43,489
Hello? Who is this?

237
00:14:44,636 --> 00:14:46,005
Didn't you save my name?

238
00:14:46,685 --> 00:14:50,152
Of course I did.

239
00:14:50,405 --> 00:14:53,133
Then why ask who it is?

240
00:14:53,541 --> 00:14:56,645
I'm sorry. I'm really sorry.

241
00:14:57,035 --> 00:14:58,235
This punk...

242
00:14:58,628 --> 00:15:00,104
Let's meet tomorrow.

243
00:15:00,835 --> 00:15:03,040
Yes, where should we meet?

244
00:15:03,539 --> 00:15:06,320
Our fateful and inevitable Café 67?

245
00:15:06,320 --> 00:15:09,000
Yes, be there by 1 p.m.
The producer will be there too.

246
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:11,021
Thank you.

247
00:15:11,528 --> 00:15:13,448
Thank you so much, writer.

248
00:15:14,827 --> 00:15:17,440
Mom, Dad, I did it!

249
00:15:18,627 --> 00:15:19,861
Congratulations, son.

250
00:15:20,579 --> 00:15:23,096
But why is that writer so cold?

251
00:15:23,429 --> 00:15:24,900
Who does she think she is,
treating you like that?

252
00:15:24,900 --> 00:15:26,917
Whether she treats me
like a rat or a loach,

253
00:15:27,968 --> 00:15:32,080
I, Seo Seung Wu,
finally get to turn this writer's novel...

254
00:15:32,080 --> 00:15:34,176
into a webtoon.

255
00:15:34,555 --> 00:15:35,555
It's too early.

256
00:15:36,008 --> 00:15:38,755
Didn't I tell you not to count
your chickens before they hatch,

257
00:15:39,328 --> 00:15:41,205
and to wait until the contract's signed
and the money's in your account?

258
00:15:42,453 --> 00:15:46,072
Why wouldn't I count my precious chickens?

259
00:15:49,743 --> 00:15:50,743
It's good.

260
00:15:55,524 --> 00:15:57,099
So, how was your date?

261
00:15:58,080 --> 00:15:59,440
It wasn't a date.

262
00:16:03,775 --> 00:16:05,856
What is it?
You've got something to tell me, right?

263
00:16:06,653 --> 00:16:09,875
As a novelist,
what do you think of an event where...

264
00:16:10,480 --> 00:16:13,435
I reconnect with someone
I met just once 25 years ago?

265
00:16:13,843 --> 00:16:16,837
We've been next to each other
all this time without even knowing it...

266
00:16:16,837 --> 00:16:19,979
Don't tell me your team manager
is the one you met 25 years ago?

267
00:16:21,111 --> 00:16:22,311
You're like a psychic.

268
00:16:22,311 --> 00:16:23,811
That's fate.

269
00:16:24,099 --> 00:16:25,357
Fate, my foot.

270
00:16:26,452 --> 00:16:28,485
Anyway, it was really strange.

271
00:16:29,152 --> 00:16:32,461
At first, things were so twisted,
we were practically enemies.

272
00:16:32,917 --> 00:16:34,507
You like him, don't you?

273
00:16:34,716 --> 00:16:37,416
Hey, no way. Why would I like him?

274
00:16:37,845 --> 00:16:41,589
What do you mean, no?
Excitement is written all over your face.

275
00:16:41,813 --> 00:16:43,424
It's not.

276
00:16:44,373 --> 00:16:47,768
And he's someone I shouldn't like.

277
00:16:48,100 --> 00:16:49,100
What do you mean?

278
00:16:49,235 --> 00:16:52,259
Actually,
there's someone who really likes him.

279
00:16:52,565 --> 00:16:53,965
She's liked him for a very long time.

280
00:16:54,821 --> 00:16:57,864
I don't think
I should get in the middle of that.

281
00:16:57,864 --> 00:17:01,448
Do you have some kind
of good-girl complex?

282
00:17:01,915 --> 00:17:03,141
Or is he married?

283
00:17:03,141 --> 00:17:06,043
Hey! Don't talk nonsense.
It's not like that.

284
00:17:08,296 --> 00:17:11,331
Based on my extensive dating experience
and my instincts as a novelist,

285
00:17:11,968 --> 00:17:14,979
and everything I've overheard
through the wall between you two...

286
00:17:14,979 --> 00:17:17,147
"Everything I've overheard?"

287
00:17:17,387 --> 00:17:18,928
What did I do?

288
00:17:18,928 --> 00:17:20,048
I heard it all.

289
00:17:21,155 --> 00:17:23,528
Dating using rehearsals as an excuse?

290
00:17:24,733 --> 00:17:27,557
You and that team manager
have already started something.

291
00:17:27,800 --> 00:17:30,075
Hey, don't say something so ridiculous.

292
00:17:30,517 --> 00:17:33,875
Don't you dare say anything weird
in front of Mom and Dad, okay?

293
00:17:35,064 --> 00:17:36,827
What does she even know?

294
00:17:48,869 --> 00:17:50,909
- Are you okay?
- Yes, I'm okay.

295
00:17:54,072 --> 00:17:55,651
You call that okay?

296
00:18:04,175 --> 00:18:05,175
That must hurt.

297
00:18:11,384 --> 00:18:12,384
That must hurt.

298
00:18:22,037 --> 00:18:24,987
Come to think of it,
he's just like back then.

299
00:18:25,612 --> 00:18:26,912
How come I didn't recognize him?

300
00:18:28,477 --> 00:18:31,363
Dad, I met that kid.

301
00:18:32,379 --> 00:18:35,648
The one I met at the playground
on my birthday.

302
00:18:37,515 --> 00:18:41,344
Back then, you praised me
for helping someone weaker.

303
00:18:43,081 --> 00:18:45,581
Come to think of it,

304
00:18:46,249 --> 00:18:49,116
that was the last time
you ever praised me.

305
00:18:57,173 --> 00:18:59,880
Who is that? You made a friend?

306
00:19:00,481 --> 00:19:02,347
She is younger than me.

307
00:19:03,072 --> 00:19:05,400
The neighborhood kids were bullying her,
so I helped.

308
00:19:05,900 --> 00:19:08,200
She said she was waiting
for her mom over there.

309
00:19:11,387 --> 00:19:14,539
Really?
You know how to help those in need now...

310
00:19:14,993 --> 00:19:16,411
You're all grown up, Gyeol.

311
00:19:18,296 --> 00:19:20,563
Let's go. I made a reservation
for your birthday dinner.

312
00:19:20,857 --> 00:19:21,857
Yes, Dad.

313
00:19:29,508 --> 00:19:32,608
Dad,
I think I have feelings for that kid...

314
00:19:36,836 --> 00:19:39,969
No, right? I'm leaving soon anyway.

315
00:19:42,489 --> 00:19:43,489
Come in.

316
00:19:45,618 --> 00:19:46,618
Grandma.

317
00:19:53,936 --> 00:19:55,939
You miss your dad a lot, don't you?

318
00:19:57,104 --> 00:19:58,541
Yes, I do.

319
00:20:00,472 --> 00:20:04,573
Let's have breakfast together
on your birthday this year.

320
00:20:05,235 --> 00:20:06,613
Grandma, I...

321
00:20:06,781 --> 00:20:10,907
I know it's hard for you
to even celebrate...

322
00:20:12,731 --> 00:20:16,205
when it's your father's
death anniversary..

323
00:20:18,227 --> 00:20:20,723
Still, this birthday...

324
00:20:23,011 --> 00:20:26,091
Who knows if we'll be able...

325
00:20:26,091 --> 00:20:29,555
to spend it together
with your grandpa next year?

326
00:20:32,185 --> 00:20:33,385
I'll think about it.

327
00:20:35,195 --> 00:20:38,936
And how about changing
your laptop password?

328
00:20:39,225 --> 00:20:41,992
Why? Did someone use my computer?

329
00:20:42,259 --> 00:20:45,027
Well, not exactly,

330
00:20:45,824 --> 00:20:47,933
but you might as well change it
since you're in the competition.

331
00:20:48,904 --> 00:20:52,309
Well, I'm sure you'll handle it yourself.

332
00:20:52,913 --> 00:20:54,713
- You should sleep.
- Yes.

333
00:20:55,264 --> 00:20:56,264
Good night, Grandma.

334
00:20:56,264 --> 00:20:57,264
- All right.
- Yes.

335
00:21:14,589 --> 00:21:18,251
By the way, how are you going to start
your first day with a cast on?

336
00:21:19,003 --> 00:21:21,981
I guess I'll have to ask the CEO
for his understanding tomorrow.

337
00:21:22,200 --> 00:21:23,667
You'll ask the CEO yourself?

338
00:21:24,619 --> 00:21:26,765
Right, your salary...

339
00:21:28,336 --> 00:21:29,536
There I go again.

340
00:21:30,284 --> 00:21:33,123
What does the salary matter?

341
00:21:34,163 --> 00:21:37,733
These days,
I should be grateful you even have a job.

342
00:21:38,792 --> 00:21:42,659
Right,
I'm thinking of renting out Eun Ae's room.

343
00:21:43,179 --> 00:21:45,928
What? Then what about Eun Ae?

344
00:21:46,181 --> 00:21:49,419
She'll just share a room
with Eun Nim again like before.

345
00:21:49,419 --> 00:21:51,219
Do you really have to go that far?

346
00:21:51,597 --> 00:21:53,667
After Eun Hyeong got married,
Eun Ae and Eun Nim...

347
00:21:53,992 --> 00:21:56,240
were so happy
to finally have separate rooms.

348
00:21:56,240 --> 00:21:58,139
They'll just have to deal with it.

349
00:21:59,933 --> 00:22:01,835
We still have a lot to do.

350
00:22:02,509 --> 00:22:05,576
Eun Ae and Eun Nim's weddings,

351
00:22:05,916 --> 00:22:07,216
and preparing for our retirement.

352
00:22:09,421 --> 00:22:11,237
I'm sorry for everything.

353
00:22:11,744 --> 00:22:14,967
Instead, let's definitely go on a trip
for your 60th birthday.

354
00:22:14,967 --> 00:22:17,392
I'll keep that promise no matter what.

355
00:22:17,571 --> 00:22:19,888
From now on,
we need to take care of our health first.

356
00:22:20,621 --> 00:22:23,467
Don't you know that health
is the greatest asset as we get older?

357
00:22:25,368 --> 00:22:28,317
I like listening to you nag like this.

358
00:22:28,597 --> 00:22:29,829
You're so easy to please.

359
00:22:32,611 --> 00:22:35,907
So, your janitor friend is starting
at the secretary's office next week?

360
00:22:36,199 --> 00:22:37,261
Yeah, but...

361
00:22:37,683 --> 00:22:40,411
he agonized over that decision so much,

362
00:22:40,411 --> 00:22:42,483
I thought I'd grow a tumor from stress.

363
00:22:43,533 --> 00:22:45,100
Unbelievable.

364
00:22:45,100 --> 00:22:48,011
Why hesitate when a friend sets you up...

365
00:22:48,195 --> 00:22:49,477
as the CEO's secretary?

366
00:22:50,725 --> 00:22:52,045
But if you think about it
from his perspective,

367
00:22:52,045 --> 00:22:54,277
it makes sense.

368
00:22:55,016 --> 00:22:57,637
A guy who used to be top of the class...

369
00:22:57,637 --> 00:23:01,115
now working as a friend's assistant
at his age. That's not easy.

370
00:23:01,115 --> 00:23:03,923
Still, it's better than cleaning.

371
00:23:04,317 --> 00:23:05,850
- True, that's true.
- Yeah.

372
00:23:06,376 --> 00:23:08,592
And speaking of which,

373
00:23:09,059 --> 00:23:11,943
how about inviting him and Gwon Sik over
next weekend,

374
00:23:11,943 --> 00:23:13,731
with their spouses?

375
00:23:14,232 --> 00:23:17,379
Invite them over? Why?

376
00:23:17,379 --> 00:23:19,741
You guys should just have dinner together.

377
00:23:19,741 --> 00:23:20,808
Come on.

378
00:23:21,419 --> 00:23:25,077
I want to show Mr. Seo that Seong Jun,

379
00:23:25,077 --> 00:23:27,728
who's even more capable than him,
is my secretary.

380
00:23:27,728 --> 00:23:30,405
It'd also be nice for the wives
to get to know each other.

381
00:23:31,799 --> 00:23:33,064
You just want to show off, don't you?

382
00:23:34,670 --> 00:23:36,070
Show off? Me?

383
00:23:36,251 --> 00:23:37,549
Well, yeah.

384
00:23:37,867 --> 00:23:40,672
Friends who were top of their class
and went to top universities...

385
00:23:40,672 --> 00:23:42,635
are now both working
as assistants for our family.

386
00:23:44,021 --> 00:23:46,459
I'll bring in a five-star hotel chef...

387
00:23:46,707 --> 00:23:48,648
and throw an amazing garden party.

388
00:23:49,301 --> 00:23:51,427
Are you out of your mind?

389
00:23:51,789 --> 00:23:53,884
Father is sick,
and you're talking about a garden party?

390
00:23:53,884 --> 00:23:55,448
Just keep it simple at home.

391
00:23:55,899 --> 00:23:57,447
Mother's cooking is great.

392
00:23:57,447 --> 00:23:58,688
Right.

393
00:23:59,072 --> 00:24:01,307
Then how about making Mother
the head chef...

394
00:24:01,489 --> 00:24:03,656
and having the housekeeper and Jeong Ran
assist her?

395
00:24:04,379 --> 00:24:07,061
Do whatever you want. What will you do?

396
00:24:07,335 --> 00:24:10,555
Me?
I'll be the general director of the party.

397
00:24:10,709 --> 00:24:14,808
I have to go to the salon,
oversee the food, the flowers...

398
00:24:15,173 --> 00:24:18,072
There's a lot for me to handle.

399
00:24:23,355 --> 00:24:25,496
Wait. Let me do it. I'll do it.

400
00:24:26,212 --> 00:24:27,680
- Seriously, you...
- Here.

401
00:24:31,216 --> 00:24:33,523
This reminds me of our newlywed days.

402
00:24:34,105 --> 00:24:36,738
You used to tie my tie like this
every morning.

403
00:24:38,149 --> 00:24:41,950
How did you not even know
how to tie a tie back then?

404
00:24:41,950 --> 00:24:43,017
There, it's done.

405
00:24:43,829 --> 00:24:46,389
It's not that I couldn't tie it.
I just liked you doing it for me.

406
00:24:46,800 --> 00:24:48,469
So I just pretended.

407
00:24:48,661 --> 00:24:49,901
What?

408
00:24:55,507 --> 00:24:58,139
Congratulations on your first day
at Kangsu Construction, Dad.

409
00:24:58,408 --> 00:25:01,720
What first day?
I've been going there all along.

410
00:25:02,108 --> 00:25:03,797
Hurry, Dad. We'll be late.

411
00:25:03,797 --> 00:25:04,893
I'll be going now.

412
00:25:05,491 --> 00:25:07,962
It's nice seeing a father and daughter
go to the same company.

413
00:25:08,384 --> 00:25:10,056
- I'm heading out too.
- Okay.

414
00:25:10,056 --> 00:25:11,400
- Take care.
- All right.

415
00:25:11,400 --> 00:25:12,693
- You too, Eun Ae.
- Yeah.

416
00:25:15,045 --> 00:25:17,805
What? To Gyeol's father's columbarium?

417
00:25:18,475 --> 00:25:22,443
I'd go myself,
but in this condition, I can't.

418
00:25:23,707 --> 00:25:27,272
So could you take Gyeol?

419
00:25:28,557 --> 00:25:31,568
Since he can't drive, use my car.

420
00:25:32,840 --> 00:25:34,301
Yes, actually today is...

421
00:25:34,301 --> 00:25:37,091
Seong Jun's first day
at the secretary's office,

422
00:25:37,574 --> 00:25:39,341
so I was going to the company
for the handoff.

423
00:25:40,131 --> 00:25:42,131
I'll take Gyeol around lunchtime.

424
00:25:42,820 --> 00:25:46,387
All right, I appreciate it.

425
00:25:50,469 --> 00:25:51,869
Why seaweed soup?

426
00:25:52,425 --> 00:25:53,813
It's Gyeol's birthday today.

427
00:25:54,481 --> 00:25:56,681
How could you not know that as his mother?

428
00:25:57,041 --> 00:26:00,525
Honestly, how is he supposed
to eat seaweed soup...

429
00:26:00,730 --> 00:26:02,130
on his father's memorial?

430
00:26:05,758 --> 00:26:09,019
He's never had a proper birthday meal
because of that.

431
00:26:09,812 --> 00:26:11,947
I made it so that won't happen anymore.

432
00:26:13,196 --> 00:26:14,196
Did you sleep well?

433
00:26:15,769 --> 00:26:16,969
Tell Gyeol to come down.

434
00:26:18,012 --> 00:26:19,229
He left early.

435
00:26:19,445 --> 00:26:22,469
Right,
and he asked me to tell you he's sorry.

436
00:26:24,523 --> 00:26:27,784
I told him so many times
to have breakfast together today.

437
00:26:31,700 --> 00:26:33,833
(Kangsu Construction)

438
00:26:37,436 --> 00:26:40,237
Where is Team Manager Ko Gyeol's seat?

439
00:26:41,252 --> 00:26:42,252
It's over here.

440
00:26:46,496 --> 00:26:47,496
Flowers?

441
00:26:48,422 --> 00:26:49,589
It's a company tradition.

442
00:26:49,712 --> 00:26:52,091
The admin team sends a flower basket
on employees' birthdays.

443
00:26:52,091 --> 00:26:54,144
What? It's his birthday today?

444
00:26:54,860 --> 00:26:57,960
Shouldn't we throw him a surprise party?

445
00:26:58,599 --> 00:27:01,032
Right. Should I go buy a cake?

446
00:27:01,146 --> 00:27:02,513
Let's just keep it low-key.

447
00:27:04,361 --> 00:27:06,147
Okay. Good morning, everyone.

448
00:27:06,811 --> 00:27:09,536
From today, let's start fresh...

449
00:27:09,703 --> 00:27:12,403
and give it our all for the second round.

450
00:27:13,789 --> 00:27:17,422
Team Manager Ko took a half-day today,
so keep that in mind.

451
00:27:17,746 --> 00:27:19,013
What? A half-day?

452
00:27:21,066 --> 00:27:22,700
(Ko Gyeol)

453
00:27:51,048 --> 00:27:52,048
Mr. Seo.

454
00:27:53,115 --> 00:27:54,115
Team Manager Ko.

455
00:28:04,433 --> 00:28:07,100
(Our Happy Days)

456
00:28:07,317 --> 00:28:09,168
- What? A studio?
- What? A studio?

457
00:28:09,168 --> 00:28:10,683
- I'm good.
- We're now...

458
00:28:10,683 --> 00:28:13,627
on the same boat. We're comrades.

459
00:28:13,627 --> 00:28:17,584
I want to see him properly settled
before I go,

460
00:28:17,584 --> 00:28:19,192
so please help him out.

461
00:28:19,192 --> 00:28:22,347
Team Manager Ko doesn't even like cake,
so you didn't have to go to the trouble.

462
00:28:22,347 --> 00:28:24,784
Well, Manager Seo
always takes good care of things.

463
00:28:24,784 --> 00:28:27,000
Still,
I wanted to congratulate him sincerely.

464
00:28:27,000 --> 00:28:28,433
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
